@startuml
title Role-Based Dashboard Access Control

actor "Admin" as A
actor "Staff" as S
actor "Guest" as G

package "Dashboard Components" {
  component "User Management" as UM
  component "Room Management" as RM
  component "Booking Management" as BM
  component "Payment Processing" as PP
  component "Analytics Dashboard" as AD
  component "Personal Profile" as PPF
}

' Admin - Full Access
A -r-> UM : Full CRUD
A -r-> RM : Full CRUD
A -r-> BM : Full CRUD
A -r-> PP : Full Access
A -r-> AD : Full Access
A -l-> PPF : View/Edit

' Staff - Limited Access
S -d-> RM : Read/Update
S -d-> BM : Read/Update
S -d-> PP : Read-only
S -d-> AD : Read-only
S -d-> PPF : View/Edit

' Guest - Minimal Access
G -u-> BM : Create/View own
G -u-> PPF : View/Edit own

note right of A
**Admin Privileges:**
- Full system control
- User role management
- All data access
- System configuration
end note

note left of S
**Staff Privileges:**
- Daily operations
- Room/booking management
- Limited reporting
- No user management
end note

note bottom of G
**Guest Privileges:**
- Personal bookings only
- Profile management
- No system access
end note

@enduml